Make a folder on Desktop > my_python_app

Make a file in that folder > app.py
#app.py
print("Hello World!")

Make another file in that folder > requirements.txt
#requirements.txt
flask

Make another docker file > Dockerfile
folder location cmd type = type nul > Dockerfile
#Dockerfile
FROM python:3.9 #change version acc to your python
WORKDIR /app
COPY . /app
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

In the same cmd type = docker buildx build -t my_python_app .
In the same cmd type = docker run my_python_app

(Local Machine Successfully Run)

*For Docker Machine*
Login to docker
Open terminal > enable
Type = docker tag my_python_app your_dockerhub_username/my_python_app:latest
eg. docker tag my_python_app peehul23/my_python_app:latest

Push Image
type = docker push your_dockerhub_username/my_python_app:latest
eg. docker push peehul23/my_python_app:latest

Pull Image
type = docker pull your_dockerhub_username/my_python_app:latest
eg. docker pull peehul23/my_python_app:latest

Run Image once pulled
type = docker run your_dockerhub_username/my_python_app
eg. docker run peehul23/my_python_app